Kabuchai Member of Parliament James Mukwe Lusweti will be buried on Saturday at his Sanandiki village home in Kabuchai Constituency, Bungoma County. 
The comical and witty politician, who was a member of Ford-Kenya party, died at a Nairobi hospital two weeks ago after a long battle with arthritis and gout.



